result.execSummary:
The defendant Jason D West was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Must report to Probation today (10/6/2015). May petition Court for early discharge.
***Per Court Order on 9/29/2022, Probation is extended by 12 months or until completion of restitution payments.***

miscConds.notes: May not possess or use firearms or potential loss of body armor.
Cannot vote until civil rights are restored. Cannot hold elected office. Other civil rights may be lost until restored. If not a U.S. Citizen may face deportation or loss of other citizenship rights.
Must provide a DNA sample. Must complete a COMPAS Evaluation and follow through. If victim wishes to meet or victim offender conference, Court will order.
Must complete an AODA assessment and compliance.

*Per Amended Restitution Order dated 10/10/2016: $16,410.96 restitution, plus a 10% surcharge of $1,641.10, for a total of $18,052.06, to be paid to Probation. Joint & Several with Tyler Chute (14CF53), John Moon (14CF105) & Shawn Thompson (14CF54).  Any unpaid amount at the time of discharge from Probation may be reduced to a civil judgment.  
**An Amended Judgment of Conviction was not generated in 2016 to reflect the Amended Restitution Order dated 10/10/2016, one is being done now to accurately reflect the restitution amounts ordered per the Amended Restitution Order and Joint and Several restitution ordered.

timeConds.notes: Banked for use by Probation Agent if necessary. Subject to work release. NO good time.
150 hours of community service for each year on Probation. Must report to Restorative Justice for community service hours.
